programme.title: Deadly Disasters: El Niño

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Tsunamis

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Cyclones
programme.desc: An intense area of low pressure that forms over warm tropical waters, tropical cyclones are responsible for some of the most catastrophic extreme weather events. Their deadly winds and torrential rain wreak destruction on an unprecedented scale.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Mosquitoes
programme.desc: In 2014, Microsoft Founder Bill Gates described the mosquito as the “deadliest animal in the world.” It is estimated by the World Health Organisation that they kill roughly 750,000 people per year.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Floods
programme.desc: Even when below your knees, you can still be swept off your feet by the torrent of water. And the danger doesn’t stop there: electric shocks, contaminated water and washed away vehicles are perilous.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Famine
programme.desc: Every continent on Earth has experienced this terrifying phenomenon at some point in its history. It’s ravaged the world for centuries, as crop infestation, drought, flooding and disease have killed thousands.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Wildfires
programme.desc: With flames roaring to heights of 50 meters or more and temperatures exceeding 1,200°C, the wildfire is one of Mother Nature’s most horrific killers. Wildfires show no signs of stopping and their inexorability on this planet is truly terrifying.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MANMADE
programme.desc: When it comes to disasters, mother nature has mankind beat. However, as mankind expands, evolves and technology advances, it comes with dangerous challenges. When errors are made or unforeseen circumstances occur, the results can be devastating.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: TORNADO
programme.desc: A tornado is a violently rotating column of air extending from the base of a thunderstorm down to the ground. Tornadoes are capable of completely destroying well-made structures, uprooting trees, and hurling objects through the air like deadly missiles.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MEGAFLOODS
programme.desc: Water covers two thirds of the earth’s surface, and we are utterly dependent on it, but when this vital ingredient of life unleashes its fury on the planet it becomes the ultimate bringer of death.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: EARTHQUAKES
programme.desc: Earthquakes happen when tectonic plates suddenly slip causing shock waves to shake the surface of the Earth. They occur on fault lines - the most active are the Ring of Fire in the Pacific Ocean and the San Andreas fault on America’s west coast.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: CONSTRUCTION
programme.desc: Bridges and tunnels have transformed the way we live, making the inaccessible easy to reach, and turning time consuming journeys into convenient commutes, but when things go wrong they can go very wrong indeed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: War Story: Sicily: The First Campaign
programme.desc: The Sicily Campaign began with the largest seaborne invasion in history on 9-10 July 1943. The Allied forces of Britain, Canada, and the United States sought to knock Italy out of the war and attack Germany from the south.

programme.title: War Story: Bomb Girls Remember
programme.desc: During the Second World War, 250,000 Canadian women helped to build the arsenal of democracy. These young women met the challenges of factory work and helped to win the Second World War, and by doing so, paved the way for future generations.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Getting Home
programme.desc: In this film, Bomber Command personnel and a Luftwaffe pilot take the viewer through the frightening reality of fighting in the skies as they try to get a damaged bomber home.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Hitting Back
programme.desc: After surviving the German bombing campaign of British cities, RAF Bomber Command struck back against Germany. The devastating consequences of raids, for both for the young men in the skies and the people on the ground, are portrayed in this film.

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: Sydney Harbour Bridge
programme.desc: The story of the world's tallest steel arched bridge.

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: Severn Bridge
programme.desc: Rob Bell reveals how the Severn Bridge was constructed.

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: Brooklyn Bridge
programme.desc: A tale of big money, corruption, ambition, death and tragedy.

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: The Millau Viaduct
programme.desc: Rob Bell meets the designers of the world's tallest bridge.

programme.title: Britain's Greatest Bridges: The Clifton Suspension Bridge
programme.desc: The story of Brunel's famous bridge over the Avon gorge.

programme.title: Britain's Greatest Bridges: The Tyne Bridge
programme.desc: Rob Bell explores the story of the Tyne Bridge.

programme.title: Britain's Greatest Bridges: Tower Bridge
programme.desc: Rob Bell uncovers the extraordinary story of Tower Bridge.

programme.title: Britain's Greatest Bridges: The Humber Bridge
programme.desc: Rob Bell tells the story of the Humber Bridge.

programme.title: Britain's Greatest Bridges: The Britannia Bridge
programme.desc: Rob Bell recounts the story of the Britannia Bridge.

programme.title: Britain's Greatest Bridges: The Forth Rail Bridge
programme.desc: The Forth Rail Bridge has grown to symbolise Scotland.

programme.title: Building Britain's Canals: Kennet and Avon
programme.desc: Dan Jones examines the Kennet and Avon canal.

programme.title: Building Britain's Canals: Grand Union Canal
programme.desc: The canal challenged the great engineering minds of its time.

programme.title: Building Britain's Canals: Leeds & Liverpool Canal
programme.desc: This canal turned Liverpool into the busiest port on Earth.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Moving Bridges
programme.desc: Moving Bridges: Exotic milestones on moveable infrastructure. Historically significant: the Kaiser Wilhelm Bridge and the Michigan Avenue bridge. Mechanically unique: the Pont Jacques, the Gateshead Millennium Bridge or the Scale Lane Bridge.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Steel Bridges
programme.desc: Steel bridges are extremely durable and multifunctional, fascinating not only due to its gigantic size but also because of the army of workers keeping the bridges in shape: whether on the historical landmark in Sydney or ultramodern mega bridges in China.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Railway Bridges
programme.desc: Railway bridges fascinate through different construction methods from masonry, truss-beam bridges to steel-concrete arch bridge. Heavier loads, faster speeds, more frequently: trains speed over bridges and the maintenance teams face ever larger challenges

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Road Bridges
programme.desc: Road bridges: gigantic constructions of modern road traffic. Europa and Ganter Bridge, Öresund bridge, Sunshine Skyway and Viaduct de Millau.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Suspension Bridges
programme.desc: Suspension bridges – impressively wide and stretched high over supporting cables or stay cables. The landscape-shaping icons: The superlative Golden Gate, Akashi Kaikyo, Aizaih, El Baluarte and Russky Bridge.

programme.title: Aliens Among Us: The Michael Wolf Theory

programme.title: The Witnesses: Ancient Alien Encounters
programme.desc: Contactee, sighter, and abductee share similar and different experiences with beings from other dimensions, leaving a lasting mark of their presence.

programme.title: UFO Hunters II: Tales from the Universe
programme.desc: Italian ufologists explore alien evidence in history & folklore. Have we been watched since ancient times?

programme.title: Unsolved Mysteries: UFO Odyssey
programme.desc: This episode includes: UFO Odyssey, Reporter's Trucker and Haunted Mansion.

programme.title: Alien Invasion: Are We Ready?: Episode 1
programme.desc: Aliens attacking Earth is the stuff of sci-fi stories, but what if it really happened? Top scientists, military strategists and authors war-game an extraordinary alien invasion scenario.

programme.title: Authentic Photographs of an Alien: The Caponi Case
programme.desc: Caponi's encounters with aliens from 1993. Real photos showcase extraterrestrial life.

programme.title: Confessions Of An Alien Abductee
programme.desc: Chantelle, Marie and Simon are all alien abductees. These ordinary people share their extraordinary stories as they seek help through the curiously named Anomalous Mind Management Abductee Contactee Helpline, or AMMACH.

programme.title: Unsolved Mysteries: Texas UFO
programme.desc: This episode includes: Scared to Death, Texas UFO, Butch Cassidy and Sibling Search & Update.

programme.title: Alien Crash Retrievals
programme.desc: Learn the shocking truth about extraterrestrial beings on planet Earth. World governments and military factions are not only aware of the Alien presence; they may be in communication with alien races.

programme.title: Area 51, Roswell Crash, Alien Abductions
programme.desc: Area 51 is located at the center of UFO research and legends of extra-terrestrial folklore. It is located six hundred miles west of Roswell, New Mexico, where the infamous Roswell UFO crashed in 1947. Also in this episode The Allagash Alien Abductions .

programme.title: Dulce Base: The New Illuminati
programme.desc: Dulce, New Mexico is a hotspot for mysterious phenomena and alleged secret military collaboration between humans and aliens.

programme.title: UFO Hunters: The Italian Ufologists
programme.desc: Italian researchers explore mass UFO sightings, clipeology, and real testimonies, delving into the history and research methods of ufology.

programme.title: Alien Mass Sightings: The Undeniable Truth
programme.desc: Documentary analyzes mass alien sightings, questions reliability of official explanations, identifies common patterns for further investigation.

programme.title: Unsolved Mysteries: Belgian UFO

programme.title: From the Mothman to the Reptilians: A Guide to Alien Species
programme.desc: Witnesses from around the world have had close encounters with extraterrestrial races, shaping our imagination and becoming cultural phenomena.

programme.title: Alien Global Threat
programme.desc: New evidence reveals that world governments have had a pact with aliens for decades and that human abductions are being allowed by government and military factions.

programme.title: A Dickens of a Holiday!
programme.desc: To make the 100th anniversary of her hometown’s Victorian festival a success, Cassie invites action movie star and former high school classmate Jake to play Scrooge in 'A Christmas Carol'.

programme.title: The Mistletoe Inn
programme.desc: Kim Ross, an aspiring romance novelist, finds herself unceremoniously dumped by her soon-to-be-published romance novelist boyfriend, Garth. She decides to take a leap and signs up for a romance writing retreat.

programme.title: Lights, Camera, Christmas!
programme.desc: When a holiday rom-com movie shooting in her town needs a costume designer, Kerry, a local shop owner, steps into the role. While working on the movie, she rediscovers her passion for costume design.

programme.title: Finding Father Christmas
programme.desc: Christmas for Miranda is a painful reminder of the family she never had. Her mother died when she was young, never revealing the identity of her father. But, three days before Christmas, she unexpectedly receives a clue.

programme.title: A Gift Wrapped Christmas
programme.desc: A personal shopper Gwen's newest client, Charlie, is a high-rolling, workaholic, single father.

programme.title: Holiday Hearts
programme.desc: While planning an annual Christmas party, Peyton is forced together with Ben to care for a friend's daughter. While finding their Christmas spirit, will there be some romance along the way?

programme.title: The Santa Stakeout
programme.desc: Tanya is a police detective who is reluctantly partnered with fellow detective Ryan to solve a recent string of heists taking place during high-profile holiday parties around town. They go undercover as newlyweds...

programme.title: A Family Christmas Gift
programme.desc: When Amber spends the holidays with her Aunt Dora and helps plan a fundraising Christmas Concert, it brings Amber closer to her aunt and a new love into her life.

programme.title: Nantucket Noel
programme.desc: During the Seaside Noel celebrations Christina learns of a developer who is planning to tear down the wharf that is home to her toy store. Tensions rise as she falls for the developer's son, Andy.

programme.title: Christmas Festival of Ice
programme.desc: When Emma finds out that her beloved ice-sculpting contest, part of her hometown's Christmas festival, has been canceled, she springs into action.

programme.title: A Christmas Tree Grows in Colorado
programme.desc: Erin is planning the town’s Christmas celebration and must win over firefighter Kevin in order to obtain the beautiful spruce tree from his property for the celebration.

programme.title: Last Chance
programme.desc: Last Chance by Paul Émile d’Entremont travels the world to tell the stories of five asylum seekers who flee their native countries to escape homophobic violence. Here in Canada, they face hurdles integrating into society and fear deportation.

programme.title: Sylvies Story
programme.desc: The film shows Sylvie in a Montréal transition house, highlighting the hurdles of violence, loneliness, and scarcity. It emphasizes sharing experiences and transition houses' support in connecting victims with legal and social aid.

programme.title: The Fate Of America
programme.desc: On Sept 13, 1759, the Battle of the Plains of Abraham sealed America's fate in 20 mins. 'The Fate of America' explores this myth, leaving French Canadians pondering defeat. Filmmaker Jacques Godbout's take unites Montcalm and Wolfe's descendants.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Needles And Pins
programme.desc: In this film about a factory seamstress, there is the substitution of glamor for genuine job satisfaction and advancement. The film was made in 1955.

programme.title: Sisters In The Struggle
programme.desc: Sisters in the Struggle features Black women who are active in community organizing, electoral politics, and labour and feminist organizing. They share their insights and personal testimonies on a legacy of racism and sexism.

programme.title: The Children Of Refus Global
programme.desc: In 1948, Borduas' manifesto marked Quebec's modernization. Filmmaker Manon Barbeau revisits, exploring its impact on descendants. Their childhoods, marked by abandonment, reveal art's transformative power in emotional reflection.

programme.title: Le Grand Serpent Du Monde
programme.desc: A young forty-something, Tom Paradise refuses to grow up. Behind the wheel of his bus he drives endlessly through the city, tracing out the path of his life, dreaming of the landscape of the American West that forever impressed him

programme.title: Perfecting The Art Of Longing
programme.desc: Using footage from security cameras, video calls and home-video archives, this experimental short film leads us on a journey through memory, family and faith, exploring the nature of connection and distance.

programme.title: Some American Feminists
programme.desc: A series of interviews, interspersed with newsreel footage, places the American feminist movement in a historical perspective. Six of the women who gave impetus to the movement discuss those issues that most concern them and which are still being debated.

programme.title: Universe
programme.desc: This cinematic masterpiece inspired Stanley Kubrick's "2001: A Space Odyssey." Realistic animation explores distant galaxies beyond the reach of telescopes, immersing viewers in awe-inspiring cosmic vistas.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Proudly She Marches
programme.desc: A recruitment film made in 1943. Its words offer women the excitement and challenge of new kinds of work in the armed services. The visual message, however, suggests that this work is merely temporary and possibly even unnatural for women.

programme.title: Mother Earth/La Terre Notre Mere
programme.desc: Mother Earth is a short, evocative, poetic film that celebrates life on our planet. This documentary film looks at the reality of human beings; the earth is our home and we are profoundly connected to all other beings.

programme.title: King Of The Hill
programme.desc: Spring 1972. The Chicago Cubs are poised to win the National League's Pennant race, lead by their star pitcher, a Black Canadian named Ferguson Jenkins, who was inducted into the Baseball Hall of Fame in 1991. This is his story.

programme.title: Proudest Girl In The World, The
programme.desc: A musical recruiting film for the Canadian Women's Army Corp.

programme.title: Men of the Deeps
programme.desc: Men of the Deeps is a moving portrait of a group of former Cape Breton miners gathered together by their love of song. They are all members of the Men of the Deeps chorus, whose performances of traditional and contemporary songs evoke their working lives

programme.title: Ryan
programme.desc: Ryan is based on the life of Ryan Larkin, a Canadian animator who, 30 years ago, produced some of the most influential animated films of his time.

programme.title: Abortion Stories From North And South
programme.desc: This film provides a historical overview of how church, state and the medical establishment have determined policies concerning abortion.

programme.title: George And Rosemary
programme.desc: George and Rosemary is an animated romantic comedy about two golden agers who prove that passion is not exclusively for the young.

programme.title: In Full Voice
programme.desc: Muslim women are disconcerting, intriguing, polarizing—and straitjacketed by conflations of ideas in front-page stories. The film sits down with six Muslim Canadian women eager to talk about what shapes their identities.

programme.title: I Want To Be An Engineer
programme.desc: This film provides a lively introduction to the professional and personal lives of three female engineers--just a few of the growing number of women who are opting for "non-traditional" jobs.

programme.title: Atonement
programme.desc: This film shows efforts being made by wildlife specialists to preserve and nurture the creatures that do remain in our wilderness areas. Scenes rarely photographed make this a spellbinding film throughout.

programme.desc: MTV Unplugged' ist der Ritterschlag für die Größten der Großen; die "Hall of Fame" des Musikfernsehens sozusagen. Nur den Besten wird die Möglichkeit geboten, ihre Songs live, akustisch, echt, ungeschönt und ungefiltert darzubieten.

programme.title: MTV Unplugged: Samy Deluxe
programme.desc: Das erste MTV Unplugged auf hoher See! Samy Deluxe setzt mit Max Herre, den Beginnern, Nena und vielen anderen die Segel auf der MS Bleichen in Hamburg für das SaMTV Unplugged.

programme.title: MTV Unplugged: Udo Lindenberg
programme.desc: Udo Lindenberg sticht ein zweites Mal für MTV Unplugged in See und hat jede Menge Leichtmatrosen an Bord, unter anderem Jan Delay, Andreas Bourani und Marteria.

programme.title: MTV Unplugged: Max Raabe
programme.desc: Im legendären Clärchens Ballhaus, Berlin nahmen Max Raabe & Palast Orchester ihr MTV Unplugged auf. Im intimen Ambiente lud er sich dazu großartige Gäste ein: Lars Eidinger, Samy Deluxe, Pawel Popolski, Lea, Mr. Lordi, Namika und Herbert Grönemeyer.

programme.title: MTV Unplugged: Peter Maffay
programme.desc: Ein MTV Unplugged-Konzert ist die Königsdisziplin für jeden Künstler. Im August 2017 nahm nun Peter Maffay sein MTV Unplugged auf. Auf der Bühne unterstützen ihn dabei u.a. Johannes Oerding, Katie Melua, Jennifer Weist & Philipp Poisel.

programme.title: Um Homem de Família
programme.desc: Jack Campbell é um solteiro convicto que há 13 anos desistiu de um grande amor para se tornar um empresário bem sucedido. Até que na véspera do Natal ele passa por uma experiência traumática e, ao acordar, vê-se numa nova vida.

programme.title: Casamento De Natal
programme.desc: Maggie é uma editora literária cujo hobby é criar oportunidades de relacionamento entre seus amigos. Quando seu ex-namorado aparece como um autor recém-contratado e bem-sucedido, Maggie precisa examinar suas decisões anteriores.

programme.title: Bebê a Bordo no Natal
programme.desc: Na sequência de “Um Ano Depois Daquele Natal”, nem todo mundo parece estar animado para o Natal da Família Chandler.

programme.title: Meu Pai é Ranzinza
programme.desc: Os animais da Fazenda Woodsley ajudam Oliver e sua irmã mais nova a chocar seu pai para abraçar o espírito natalino enquanto tentam salvar a fazenda.

programme.title: Um Natal Encantado
programme.desc: Hugo, de doze anos, ainda acredita em elfos, mas é provocado por seus colegas, então decide se forçar a crescer. Mas quando sua família sai de férias de Natal, ele descobre que elfos moram no hotel.

programme.title: Tempo de Natal
programme.desc: Dois irmãos distantes tentam se reconectar no Natal, mas há algo que um deles não consegue superar: o outro pensa que é um viajante do tempo.

programme.title: Véspera de Natal
programme.desc: É véspera de Natal e um apagão vai obrigar alguns nova-iorquinos ocupados a ficarem presos dentro de elevadores enquanto esperam por ajuda. Essa longa noite juntos irá mudar suas vidas para sempre.

programme.title: De Repente o Amor Acontece
programme.desc: Sadie, uma executiva de marketing de sucesso, é filha dos donos de uma tradicional loja de chocolates. Ao decidir passar o Natal com a família, descobre que seus pais planejam vender a loja, colocando em risco seu sonho de um dia herdá-la.

programme.title: Sobrevivendo Às Festas com Parentes
programme.desc: As irmãs Miranda e Lyla se reúnem para o Natal com suas famílias. Ao longo de três dias, alegria e caos causam estragos nos planos de férias das famílias e as antigas rivalidades entre irmãos surgem para sabotar a esperança diversão de fim de ano.

programme.title: Só Pode Ser Amor
programme.desc: Durante a temporada de Natal, três irmãs terão que decidir o que fazer com sua vida romântica quando partem para encontrar a família para as festas e seus respectivos pares surgem na cidade para tentar uma segunda chance.

programme.title: Novios por navidad
programme.desc: La organizadora de eventos Valeria, traicionada por su amiga Tere que le robó a su prometido, finge un romance con Camilo para vengarse, lo que desemboca en una inesperada historia de amor navideña.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: Intercambio navideño
programme.desc: Las gemelas Maya y Ana, separadas al nacer y con vidas totalmente distintas, se descubren e intercambian vidas por una noche, alterando sus destinos para siempre.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: Un Papá para Navidad
programme.desc: Rebeca, una estrella de las redes sociales enfocada en la fama, recibe una sorpresa cuando un desconocido, que dice ser su padre, aparece en Navidad.

programme.title: Navidad en cuatro patas
programme.desc: Maggie y Jack, dos personas solteras, tratan de regalar un perro a sus hijos de Navidad. Su lucha por la custodia de un mismo animal, les lleva a hacer algo que nunca hubieran esperado: enamorarse.

programme.title: El Deseo de Charlie
programme.desc: Un veterano militar regresa a casa después de estar ausente por estrés postraumático. Con su nuevo perro, descubre en medio de la Navidad un nuevo propósito en su vida: ayudar a los exmilitares que necesitan ayuda

programme.title: Mi amor en navidad
programme.desc: Lucas, un famoso cantante cuyo mayor éxito ha sido "Mi Amor en Navidad", decide tomarse un descanso, volviendo a su pueblo natal para pasar las fiestas. Allí se reencuentra con Elisa, su primer amor y la inspiración de su éxito navideño.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos
programme.desc: Baxter es fotógrafo y ha recibido un premio en metálico. Con él puede pagar la boda con su novia, pero a medida que va surtiendo de regalos a gente necesitada ese dinero merma, y su chica se enfada.

programme.title: Bailey: Un héroe de Navidad
programme.desc: Es "tiempo de Navidad" y Bailey preocupado de que no recibirá regalos porque ha sido un mal perrito, aprende acerca de un misterioso indio nativo americano que puede ser capaz de hacer que sus deseos se hagan realidad.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Navidad en la calle Chestnut
programme.desc: Una tienda decide iniciar un concurso para vender 60.000 luces navideñas, ordenadas por accidente. La competencia se vuelve extrema, pero la dueña de la tienda quiere mantener la competencia.

programme.title: Novios por navidad
programme.desc: La organizadora de eventos Valeria, traicionada por su amiga Tere que le robó a su prometido, finge un romance con Camilo para vengarse, lo que desemboca en una inesperada historia de amor navideña.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: Intercambio navideño
programme.desc: Las gemelas Maya y Ana, separadas al nacer y con vidas totalmente distintas, se descubren e intercambian vidas por una noche, alterando sus destinos para siempre.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: Un Papá para Navidad
programme.desc: Rebeca, una estrella de las redes sociales enfocada en la fama, recibe una sorpresa cuando un desconocido, que dice ser su padre, aparece en Navidad.

programme.title: Navidad en cuatro patas
programme.desc: Maggie y Jack, dos personas solteras, tratan de regalar un perro a sus hijos de Navidad. Su lucha por la custodia de un mismo animal, les lleva a hacer algo que nunca hubieran esperado: enamorarse.

programme.title: El Deseo de Charlie
programme.desc: Un veterano militar regresa a casa después de estar ausente por estrés postraumático. Con su nuevo perro, descubre en medio de la Navidad un nuevo propósito en su vida: ayudar a los exmilitares que necesitan ayuda

programme.title: Mi amor en navidad
programme.desc: Lucas, un famoso cantante cuyo mayor éxito ha sido "Mi Amor en Navidad", decide tomarse un descanso, volviendo a su pueblo natal para pasar las fiestas. Allí se reencuentra con Elisa, su primer amor y la inspiración de su éxito navideño.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos
programme.desc: Baxter es fotógrafo y ha recibido un premio en metálico. Con él puede pagar la boda con su novia, pero a medida que va surtiendo de regalos a gente necesitada ese dinero merma, y su chica se enfada.

programme.title: Bailey: Un héroe de Navidad
programme.desc: Es "tiempo de Navidad" y Bailey preocupado de que no recibirá regalos porque ha sido un mal perrito, aprende acerca de un misterioso indio nativo americano que puede ser capaz de hacer que sus deseos se hagan realidad.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Navidad en la calle Chestnut
programme.desc: Una tienda decide iniciar un concurso para vender 60.000 luces navideñas, ordenadas por accidente. La competencia se vuelve extrema, pero la dueña de la tienda quiere mantener la competencia.

programme.title: Novios por navidad
programme.desc: La organizadora de eventos Valeria, traicionada por su amiga Tere que le robó a su prometido, finge un romance con Camilo para vengarse, lo que desemboca en una inesperada historia de amor navideña.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: Intercambio navideño
programme.desc: Las gemelas Maya y Ana, separadas al nacer y con vidas totalmente distintas, se descubren e intercambian vidas por una noche, alterando sus destinos para siempre.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: Un Papá para Navidad
programme.desc: Rebeca, una estrella de las redes sociales enfocada en la fama, recibe una sorpresa cuando un desconocido, que dice ser su padre, aparece en Navidad.

programme.title: Navidad en cuatro patas
programme.desc: Maggie y Jack, dos personas solteras, tratan de regalar un perro a sus hijos de Navidad. Su lucha por la custodia de un mismo animal, les lleva a hacer algo que nunca hubieran esperado: enamorarse.

programme.title: El Deseo de Charlie
programme.desc: Un veterano militar regresa a casa después de estar ausente por estrés postraumático. Con su nuevo perro, descubre en medio de la Navidad un nuevo propósito en su vida: ayudar a los exmilitares que necesitan ayuda

programme.title: Mi amor en navidad
programme.desc: Lucas, un famoso cantante cuyo mayor éxito ha sido "Mi Amor en Navidad", decide tomarse un descanso, volviendo a su pueblo natal para pasar las fiestas. Allí se reencuentra con Elisa, su primer amor y la inspiración de su éxito navideño.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos
programme.desc: Baxter es fotógrafo y ha recibido un premio en metálico. Con él puede pagar la boda con su novia, pero a medida que va surtiendo de regalos a gente necesitada ese dinero merma, y su chica se enfada.

programme.title: Bailey: Un héroe de Navidad
programme.desc: Es "tiempo de Navidad" y Bailey preocupado de que no recibirá regalos porque ha sido un mal perrito, aprende acerca de un misterioso indio nativo americano que puede ser capaz de hacer que sus deseos se hagan realidad.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: Navidad en la calle Chestnut
programme.desc: Una tienda decide iniciar un concurso para vender 60.000 luces navideñas, ordenadas por accidente. La competencia se vuelve extrema, pero la dueña de la tienda quiere mantener la competencia.

programme.title: Überleben in der Savanne
programme.desc: Der Etosha-Nationalpark im Norden Namibias mit seiner trockenen Salzpfanne ist eines der bedeutendsten Wildreservate Afrikas. Nahrung und Wasser sind für die Tiere jedoch ein knappes Gut. Zu Etoshas Wildtierpopulation gehören unter anderem Elefanten, Löwen, Spitzmaulnashörner und hunderte Vogelarten. Die karge Vegetation stellt sie jedoch vor extreme Herausforderungen. Und die Plätze an den wenigen und weit verstreute Wasserlöchern sind hart umkämpft.

programme.title: Sharkville
programme.desc: Der Weiße Hai ist ein beeindruckendes Raubtier, dessen Tötungskraft gut dokumentiert und auf der ganzen Welt beobachtet wird. Der Wissenschaftler Ryan Johnson beginnt mit einer sechsjährigen Studie, um etwas mehr über das geheimnisvolle Leben des großen Weißen zu enthüllen.

programme.title: Kanadas Küstenwölfe

Das besondere an ihnen ist, dass sie nicht nur an Land jagen, sondern auch im Ozean. Die Dokumentation begleitet Naturführer Cal Humchitt und sein Team auf den Spuren der Küstenwölfe.

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana
programme.desc: Im Herzen der Maremma, der Küstenregion der Toskana, werden auf einer Azienda seit mehr als 1000 Jahren Rinder und Pferde gezüchtet. Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: Das ayurvedische Wissen wird seit Jahrhunderten in den Familien der Vaidijas bewahrt - und auch von der Schulmedizin akzeptiert und praktiziert. Krankheiten wie Arthritis oder Diabetes entstehen gemäß Ayurveda durch toxische Stoffe, wenn die drei biophysiologischen Kräfte des Körpers - die sogenannten Doshas - aus dem Gleichgewicht geraten.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Tiere, die in Europa Abscheu und Ekel verursachen, werden in Kambodscha gejagt, gegessen oder zum Verzehr verkauft. Jedes Jahr während der Regenzeit steigt das Wasser des Tonl? Sap Sees um viele Meter. Im September machen die Fischer daher immer weniger Fänge. Deshalb weichen sie auf Ratten aus: Die Tiere leben bei Hochwasser auf den Bäumen und ernähren sich von Früchten.

programme.title: Yoga
programme.desc: Es heißt, Yoga werde in Indien schon seit rund 5000 Jahren praktiziert. Doch unter der britischen Kolonialherrschaft geriet das Wissen um die medizinischen Heilkräfte von Yoga nahezu in Vergessenheit. In den 1930er Jahren entwickelte der Yoga-Meister B.K.S. Iyengar aus der altindischen Hatha-Tradition neue Techniken. Iyengar-Yoga wird inzwischen weltweit praktiziert und anerkannt.

programme.title: Vietnam
programme.desc: Im vietnamesischen Dorf Vinh Son lebt ein Großteil der Einwohner von der Schlangenzucht: Kobras, Gebänderte Rattenschlangen und sogar die extrem großen und giftigen Königskobras werden hier gehalten und verkauft - zumeist an den Nachbarn China. Der Vorsitzende des örtlichen Zuchtverbandes Kim Van Hoc war einer der ersten, der das lukrative Geschäft noch zu kommunistischen Zeiten entwickelte.

programme.title: Insekten

Heute ernähren sich bereits zwei Milliarden Menschen von den kleinen Krabbeltieren, vornehmlich in Afrika und Asien. Und langsam kommt auch Europa auf den Geschmack.

programme.title: Eliane Elias
programme.desc: There's no question about it: with a Grammy for Best Latin Jazz Album for her recording ‘Made In Brazil', seven previous Grammy nominations, four ‘Gold Disc Awards', and three ‘Best Vocal Album Awards' in Japan, Eliane Elias has taken her place in the pantheon of music giants. In her projects, Elias wears many hats: she serves as producer, composer, lyricist, arranger, pianist, and vocalist. In this concert broadcast, recorded live at the Philharmonie in Munich, Elias shows her distinctive and immediately recognizable musical style, which blends her Brazilian samba roots and her sensuous, alluring voice with her impressive instrumental bebop, jazz, classical, and compositional skills. She is an artist beyond category, and in this concert she performs with Jay Randall Anderson (bass) and Adam Nussbaum (drums).

programme.title: Cannonball Adderley
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Thelonious Monk, Charlie Rouse, Ben Riley & Larry Gales
programme.desc: The idiosyncratic pianist and composer Thelonious Monk (1917-1982) is one of the all-time greats of jazz. His music went largely misunderstood for the first 15 years of his career, after which he was rightly hailed as a genius, and received credit as a founding father of bebop. Several concerts from his 1966 European tour were recorded for television, featuring his quartet of Charles Rouse (tenor saxophone), Lawrence Gales (bass) and Benjamin Riley (drums). His quartet performed Epistrophy, 'Round Midnight, and Lulu's Back in Town in Warsaw for Polish television on April 4, 1966. On April 17, the same quartet performed a short set in Copenhagen for Danish television, featuring Lulu's Back in Town, Don't Blame Me, and Epistrophy.

programme.title: Gerry Mulligan, Dave Glenn, Harold Danko & Ed Neumeister
programme.sub-title: Gerry Mulligan Big Band - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1982, American saxophonist Gerry Mulligan gave an unforgettable performance at the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague. Mulligan was one of the leading arrangers of the cool jazz era, who worked with Miles Davis, Stan Kenton and Claude Thornhill in the 1950s and 1960s. Mulligan's early pianoless 1950s quartet with trumpeter Chet Baker is still regarded as one of the finest groups in cool jazz. Born in New York in 1927, Mulligan spent his life composing, arranging and playing jazz until his death on January 20, 1996.

programme.title: Ted Curson
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

programme.title: John Coltrane, McCoy Tyner, Elvin Jones & Jimmy Garrison
programme.desc: The mere mention of the name John Coltrane evokes a deeply emotional, often spiritual response from even the most casual jazz fan. Dexter Gordon was a fantastic saxophonist. Miles Davis was a genius. Coltrane stood above - he was a visionary, a saint-like figure. By the standards of most jazz musicians, his life was uneventful. Sure, he had a heroin habit for a while, and Miles Davis punched him, but once he'd experienced the “spiritual awakening” described in the liner notes of his 1965 album A Love Supreme, he dedicated himself to his music with extreme single-mindedness. This broadcast of Coltrane's 1965 performance at the short-lived Belgian jazz festival in Comblain-la-Tour features Trane's classic quartet with Elvin Jones (drums), Jimmy Garrison (bass) and McCoy Tyner (piano).

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, West Of The West
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Dave Brubeck Trio, Cannonball Adderley Quintet, Charles Mingus Sextet & Jimmy Smith
programme.sub-title: Smith, Adderley, Brubeck, Mingus - Newport Jazz F.
programme.desc: The Newport Jazz Festival, first established in the North-American town of Newport, Rhode Island in the summer of 1954, has now grown to become one of the largest multi-day celebrations of jazz worldwide. It has resulted in numerous famous live albums from top-rate jazz stars, and has spawned several worldwide tours, including editions of the Newport Jazz Festival in Rotterdam, The Netherlands. In October 1972, an outstanding lineup played shoulder-to-shoulder at the 7th Newport Jazz Festival held in Rotterdam's then-recently built concert venue De Doelen. These four masterful groups consisted of alto saxophonist "Cannonball" Adderley and his quintet (Nat Adderley on cornet, George Duke on keyboards, Walter Booker on bass, and Roy McCurdy on drums), Hammond organist Jimmy Smith and his band (Art Farmer on flugelhorn, Illinois Jacquet on tenor saxophone, Kenny Burrell on guitar, Clark Terry on trumpet, and Roy Haynes on drums), pianist Dave Brubeck and his trio (Jack Six on bass, Alan Dawson on drums) with accompaniment from Paul Desmond on alto saxophone and Gerry Mulligan on baritone saxophone, and bassist Charles Mingus and his group (Joe Gardner on trumpet, Hamiet Bluiett on baritone saxophone, John Foster on piano, Roy Brooks on drums) with the great high-note trumpeter Cat Anderson as a guest.

programme.title: B.B.King
programme.sub-title: B.B. King Orchestra - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Back in 1979, legendary American blues guitarist B.B. King gave an unforgettable performance for the audience in The Hague. Born in 1925 in a small town in Mississippi, 'Lucille' (as he nicknamed his guitar) helped him escape a miserable existence picking cotton. He arrived in Memphis in the late 1940s, where his cousin Bukka White taught him the tricks of the blues. Soon he developed his own style. King's virtuoso, narrative solos with lots of vibrato, have been an inspiration for most (rock) guitarists after him.

programme.title: Philippe Herreweghe, Collegium Vocale Gent, Dorothee Mields & Thomas Hobbs
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe conducts his Collegium Vocale Gent in this chamber music program dedicated to the music of J. S. Bach. On the program are Bach's Orchestral Suite No. 4 in D major, BWV 1069 Gott der Herr ist Sonn und Schild, BWV 79 and Missa brevis in G major, BWV 236. The soloists are soprano Dorothee Mields, tenor Thomas Hobbs, countertenor Alex Potter, and bass Peter Kooij. The program continues with a fine selection of Bach's works performed by French lutenist Thomas Dunford. On the program are Suite for lute in G minor, BWV 995 Suite for solo cello in G major (arr. for lute), BWV 1007 and Chaconne from Partita for solo violin in D minor (arr. lute), BWV 1004. This concert was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, in 2017.

programme.title: Philippe Herreweghe, Collegium Vocale Gent, Dorothee Mields & Thomas Hobbs
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe conducts his Collegium Vocale Gent in this chamber music program dedicated to the music of J. S. Bach. On the program are Bach's Orchestral Suite No. 4 in D major, BWV 1069 Gott der Herr ist Sonn und Schild, BWV 79 and Missa brevis in G major, BWV 236. The soloists are soprano Dorothee Mields, tenor Thomas Hobbs, countertenor Alex Potter, and bass Peter Kooij. programme.title: Raphael Pichon, Ensemble Pygmalion, Sabine Devieilhe & Arnaud de Pasquale
programme.sub-title: Mozart - A Gala for the Weber Sisters
programme.desc: On March 23, 1783, Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart gave a successful concert at Vienna's Burgtheater that he dedicated to two sopranos: Aloysia and Josepha Weber, the sisters of his wife Constanze. The concert's program would be considered odd by today's standards. The composer's Symphony No. 35 was broken up and interspersed with other compositions, such as concertos, arias, and works for solo piano. Nearly two and a half centuries later, French soprano Sabine Devieilhe, conductor Raphaël Pichon and his Ensemble Pygmalion bring a wonderful concert inspired by that remarkable event. The program includes: ‘Allegro con spirito' of Symphony No. 35, also known as the Haffner Symphony ‘Vorrei spiegarvi, oh Dio', KV 418 ‘Schon lacht der holde Frühling', KV 580 Trio of ‘Die Schlittenfahrt' No. 3, KV 605 Deutscher Tanz No. 6, KV 571 ‘Der Hölle Rache kocht in meinem Herzen' from Mozart's opera Die Zauberflöte ‘Finale: Presto' of Symphony No. 35 ‘Nehmt meinen Dank', KV 383 and ‘Dans un bois solitaire et sombre', KV 308. This performance was recorded at Théâtre Impérial de Compiègne, in Compiègne, France.

programme.title: Jodie Devos, Anaik Morel & David Violi
programme.sub-title: Tribute to French Romanticism at Venice
programme.desc: Salon Romantique à Venise salutes the work of the Palazzetto Bru Zane foundation which aims to contribute to the rediscovery of a neglected part of the French musical heritage running from Louis XVi to WW I. This concert offers a journey into the French romantic repertoire performed by pianist David Violi (piano), Jodie Devos (soprano) and Anaik Morel (mezzo-soprano). The program contains some of the most beloved French arias, such as 'Seguedille' from Bizet's Carmen by Bizet, the Flower Duet from Delibes' Lakmé and 'Mon cœur s'ouvre à ta voix' from Saint-Saëns Samson et Dalila. Recorded at the Palazzetoo Bru Zane in Venice, Italy in 2016.

programme.title: Rodolfo Mederos, Otros Aires, Teresa Parodi & Café de los Maestros
programme.desc: For the audience in the famous ballroom El Palacio in Buenos Aires, the year 2012 began with tango rhythms and Argentinean folk music. This festive broadcast opens with a tango performance by dance partners Eduardo and Gloria, accompanied by the renowned ensemble Café de los Maestros. Another highlights is a performance by bandoneon player Rodolfo Mederos and his trio. In addition, the concert features a performance by Teresa Parodi, former lead singer of the Astor Piazzolla Band, accompanied by the Fernando Suárez Paz Quintet. Also on the bill is the contemporary electronic tango formation Otros Aires. Founded by Miguel Di Genova in 2003, Otros Aires combines electronic rhythms and traditional tango instruments, such as the bandoneon, piano, and guitar. On the program are compositions by Astor Piazzolla, Pedro Maffia, Pedro Laurenz, Gustavo Mozzi, and many others. Enjoy this concert of music and dance, featuring some of Argentine's tango scene's finest artists!

programme.title: Federico Guglielmo & Roberto Loreggian
programme.sub-title: Works by Matteis, Tartini, Bach & Vivaldi
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Federico Guglielmo (violin) and Roberto Loreggian (harpsichord) present Baroque music. On the program are Nicola Matteis's Passaggio rotto e Andamento veloce per violino solo (from Ayres for the Violini), Giuseppe Tartini's Sonata in G minor Op. 1 No. 10 (B.g10) “Didone abbandonata”, J. S. Bach's Concerto in F major for solo harpsichord, BWV 978 (a transcription of Antonio Vivaldi's Violin Concerto in G major, Op. 3 No. 3, RV 310), and Vivaldi's Sonata IV in D major, RV 755.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - String Quartet No. 7 & 13, and Op. 133
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 7 in F major, Op. 59, No. 1, known as “Razumovsky” String Quartet No. 13 in B-flat major, Op. 130 and the monumental Great Fugue, Op. 133. This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 12, 2020.

Arriving just at dawn, you'll enjoy a stunning golden sunrise and rainbow, followed by a couple hours of beautiful beach scenes as you explore the beautiful resort surroundings. programme.title: Dolphin Voyage Relaxation
programme.desc: Replace your worries with wonder as you journey into the deep blue calming ocean with a pod of friendly dolphins in this new 1-hour long film. "Dolphin Voyage Relaxation" is 1-hour long and features some spectacular underwater cinematography by Peter Schneider and a synergistic blend of audio including underwater nature sounds, calming ambient music by The Cynic Project, and a subtle background layer of harmonically tuned binaural relaxation sounds by Schmidt. The result is an immersive, awe-inspiring adventure with gracefully transitions, leaving the viewer with a powerful dose of calm and healing energy direct from Nature.

programme.title: A Day in Santorini
programme.desc: Turn any screen into a window the the Greek Islands with this immensely relaxing HD visual journey through the unique and beautiful coastal village of Oia, found on the far tip of Santorini Island. Slowly awaken your senses as the morning sun rises over the sea, and watch as day slowly passes into dusk. Distant waves break and birds chirp adding an a nice ambient music that combines to create a video that's so relaxing it's almost trance-inducing.

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana
programme.desc: Im Herzen der Maremma, der Küstenregion der Toskana, werden auf einer Azienda seit mehr als 1000 Jahren Rinder und Pferde gezüchtet. Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: Das ayurvedische Wissen wird seit Jahrhunderten in den Familien der Vaidijas bewahrt - und auch von der Schulmedizin akzeptiert und praktiziert. Krankheiten wie Arthritis oder Diabetes entstehen gemäß Ayurveda durch toxische Stoffe, wenn die drei biophysiologischen Kräfte des Körpers - die sogenannten Doshas - aus dem Gleichgewicht geraten.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Tiere, die in Europa Abscheu und Ekel verursachen, werden in Kambodscha gejagt, gegessen oder zum Verzehr verkauft. Jedes Jahr während der Regenzeit steigt das Wasser des Tonl? Sap Sees um viele Meter. Im September machen die Fischer daher immer weniger Fänge. Deshalb weichen sie auf Ratten aus: Die Tiere leben bei Hochwasser auf den Bäumen und ernähren sich von Früchten.

programme.title: Yoga
programme.desc: Es heißt, Yoga werde in Indien schon seit rund 5000 Jahren praktiziert. Doch unter der britischen Kolonialherrschaft geriet das Wissen um die medizinischen Heilkräfte von Yoga nahezu in Vergessenheit. In den 1930er Jahren entwickelte der Yoga-Meister B.K.S. Iyengar aus der altindischen Hatha-Tradition neue Techniken. Iyengar-Yoga wird inzwischen weltweit praktiziert und anerkannt.

programme.title: Vietnam
programme.desc: Im vietnamesischen Dorf Vinh Son lebt ein Großteil der Einwohner von der Schlangenzucht: Kobras, Gebänderte Rattenschlangen und sogar die extrem großen und giftigen Königskobras werden hier gehalten und verkauft - zumeist an den Nachbarn China. Der Vorsitzende des örtlichen Zuchtverbandes Kim Van Hoc war einer der ersten, der das lukrative Geschäft noch zu kommunistischen Zeiten entwickelte.

programme.title: Insekten
programme.desc: In der Natur gehören Insekten seit jeher auf den Speiseplan. Nur der Mensch macht vielerorts lange einen Bogen um sie. programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [조선왕릉 가을 숲길] 인현왕후의 눈물이 서린 곳, 서오릉
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널고양의 서오릉은 서쪽에 5기의 능(경릉, 창릉, 익릉, 홍릉, 명릉)이 있다하여 이름 붙여졌습니다. 두번째로 규모가 큰 조선왕실의 왕릉군으로 모두 둘러보려면 2~3시간은 족히 걸릴만큼 묘역이 매우 큰데요. '신림(神林)'이라 불릴 만큼 자연경관이 잘 보존되어 있는 울창한 왕릉의 숲길을 걸어보세요. ※ 고양 서오릉 (사적 제198호) / 조선왕릉 (2009년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [신비롭고 아름다운 비경] 청송 주산지 EP.4
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널주산지는 조선 경종(1720년) 10월에 준공하였습니다. 주산지의 맑은 물은 주산현 꼭대기 별바위에서 계곡을 따라 흘러 주산지에 머무르고 주왕산 영봉에서 뻗친 울창한 수림으로 둘러싸여 있으며, 물위에 떠있는 듯한 왕버들과 어우러져 별천지에 온 것 같이 한적하면서도 아늑한 분위기를 자아냅니다. ※ 청송 주산지 일원 (명승 제 105호) / 청송세계지질공원 (2017년 유네스코 세계지질공원)

programme.title: 파도와 자갈의 울림. 완도 정도리 구계등
programme.desc: 바다로 내려가는 자갈 해안이 마치 아홉 개의 계단처럼 보인다는 이야기가 전해지는 구계등. 동글동글한 갯돌들의 도르르 노랫소리는 맑은 날은 아름답고, 비가 오고 파도가 거센 날이면 우레 같은 소리가 납니다. 다도해 위로 붉은 해가 떠오를 때, 방풍림을 따라 걷다 들려오는 갯돌들의 하모니를 아름다운 영상으로 만나보세요. ※ 완도 정도리 구계등 (명승 제3호)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 소리에 녹아든 삶. 제주민요
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널제주민요는 제주 사람들의 생활이 고달픈 노동과 맞닿아 있어 이를 이겨내고자 부르던 노동요가 많으며 서정적이면서도 구슬프고 한스러운 느낌이 강합니다. 맷돌을 돌리며 부르는 노래는 제주도만의 토속성을 가장 잘 담고 있는 제주민요로 꼽힙니다. 제주 특유의 향토적인 소리를 만나 봅시다. (강문희 / 국가무형문화재 제주민요 전수교육사)

programme.title: 봄을 맞이하다. 궁중병과 봄차림상
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널봄과 가장 잘 어울리는 완벽한 간식, 궁중병과를 만드는 소리를 담아봤습니다. 봄향기 가득한 화사한 진달래로 만드는 진달래 화전, 다양한 재료로 예쁘게 색을 낸 삼색쌀강정, 그리고 달콤하고 톡 쏘는 오미자 화채를 만드는 모습을 함께 감상해보시죠. (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: 전통을 담고 맛을 잇다. 장 담그기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널한국 음식의 맛은 장이 결정한다고 할 정도로 옛 조상들은 장맛이 좋지 않으면 좋은 재료를 사용해도 좋은 요리가 될 수 없다고 하였습니다. 콩 재배, 메주 만들기, 장 만들기, 장 가르기, 숙성과 발효 등으로 이어지는 중국이나 일본과 구별되는 우리나라의 독특한 제작과정을 영상으로 만나보세요. (이정숙 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: 작품이 되기 위한 인고의 시간. 바닥파기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널벼루는 물을 붓고 먹을 가는 돌을 말합니다. 단양 자석벼루는 붉은색을 띄는 원석으로 만들어집니다. 자석벼루장인이 벼루를 만들어내기 위해 바닥을 파내는 과정을 영상으로 담았습니다. 장인의 집요하고 끈기있는 벼루 제작과정을 ASMR영상을 통하여 함께 만나보시죠. (신재민 / 충북무형문화재 자석벼루장 전승교육사)

programme.title: Eliane Elias
programme.desc: There's no question about it: with a Grammy for Best Latin Jazz Album for her recording ‘Made In Brazil', seven previous Grammy nominations, four ‘Gold Disc Awards', and three ‘Best Vocal Album Awards' in Japan, Eliane Elias has taken her place in the pantheon of music giants. In her projects, Elias wears many hats: she serves as producer, composer, lyricist, arranger, pianist, and vocalist. In this concert broadcast, recorded live at the Philharmonie in Munich, Elias shows her distinctive and immediately recognizable musical style, which blends her Brazilian samba roots and her sensuous, alluring voice with her impressive instrumental bebop, jazz, classical, and compositional skills. She is an artist beyond category, and in this concert she performs with Jay Randall Anderson (bass) and Adam Nussbaum (drums).

programme.title: Thelonious Monk, Charlie Rouse, Ben Riley & Larry Gales
programme.desc: The idiosyncratic pianist and composer Thelonious Monk (1917-1982) is one of the all-time greats of jazz. His music went largely misunderstood for the first 15 years of his career, after which he was rightly hailed as a genius, and received credit as a founding father of bebop. Several concerts from his 1966 European tour were recorded for television, featuring his quartet of Charles Rouse (tenor saxophone), Lawrence Gales (bass) and Benjamin Riley (drums). His quartet performed Epistrophy, 'Round Midnight, and Lulu's Back in Town in Warsaw for Polish television on April 4, 1966. On April 17, the same quartet performed a short set in Copenhagen for Danish television, featuring Lulu's Back in Town, Don't Blame Me, and Epistrophy.

programme.title: Gerry Mulligan, Dave Glenn, Harold Danko & Ed Neumeister
programme.sub-title: Gerry Mulligan Big Band - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1982, American saxophonist Gerry Mulligan gave an unforgettable performance at the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague. Mulligan was one of the leading arrangers of the cool jazz era, who worked with Miles Davis, Stan Kenton and Claude Thornhill in the 1950s and 1960s. Mulligan's early pianoless 1950s quartet with trumpeter Chet Baker is still regarded as one of the finest groups in cool jazz. Born in New York in 1927, Mulligan spent his life composing, arranging and playing jazz until his death on January 20, 1996.

programme.title: Ted Curson

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

programme.title: John Coltrane, McCoy Tyner, Elvin Jones & Jimmy Garrison
programme.desc: The mere mention of the name John Coltrane evokes a deeply emotional, often spiritual response from even the most casual jazz fan. Dexter Gordon was a fantastic saxophonist. Miles Davis was a genius. Coltrane stood above - he was a visionary, a saint-like figure. By the standards of most jazz musicians, his life was uneventful. Sure, he had a heroin habit for a while, and Miles Davis punched him, but once he'd experienced the “spiritual awakening” described in the liner notes of his 1965 album A Love Supreme, he dedicated himself to his music with extreme single-mindedness. This broadcast of Coltrane's 1965 performance at the short-lived Belgian jazz festival in Comblain-la-Tour features Trane's classic quartet with Elvin Jones (drums), Jimmy Garrison (bass) and McCoy Tyner (piano).

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, West Of The West
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Dave Brubeck Trio, Cannonball Adderley Quintet, Charles Mingus Sextet & Jimmy Smith
programme.sub-title: Smith, Adderley, Brubeck, Mingus - Newport Jazz F.
programme.desc: The Newport Jazz Festival, first established in the North-American town of Newport, Rhode Island in the summer of 1954, has now grown to become one of the largest multi-day celebrations of jazz worldwide. It has resulted in numerous famous live albums from top-rate jazz stars, and has spawned several worldwide tours, including editions of the Newport Jazz Festival in Rotterdam, The Netherlands. In October 1972, an outstanding lineup played shoulder-to-shoulder at the 7th Newport Jazz Festival held in Rotterdam's then-recently built concert venue De Doelen. These four masterful groups consisted of alto saxophonist "Cannonball" Adderley and his quintet (Nat Adderley on cornet, George Duke on keyboards, Walter Booker on bass, and Roy McCurdy on drums), Hammond organist Jimmy Smith and his band (Art Farmer on flugelhorn, Illinois Jacquet on tenor saxophone, Kenny Burrell on guitar, Clark Terry on trumpet, and Roy Haynes on drums), pianist Dave Brubeck and his trio (Jack Six on bass, Alan Dawson on drums) with accompaniment from Paul Desmond on alto saxophone and Gerry Mulligan on baritone saxophone, and bassist Charles Mingus and his group (Joe Gardner on trumpet, Hamiet Bluiett on baritone saxophone, John Foster on piano, Roy Brooks on drums) with the great high-note trumpeter Cat Anderson as a guest.

programme.title: B.B.King
programme.sub-title: B.B. King Orchestra - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Back in 1979, legendary American blues guitarist B.B. King gave an unforgettable performance for the audience in The Hague. Born in 1925 in a small town in Mississippi, 'Lucille' (as he nicknamed his guitar) helped him escape a miserable existence picking cotton. He arrived in Memphis in the late 1940s, where his cousin Bukka White taught him the tricks of the blues. Soon he developed his own style. King's virtuoso, narrative solos with lots of vibrato, have been an inspiration for most (rock) guitarists after him.

programme.title: Philippe Herreweghe, Collegium Vocale Gent, Dorothee Mields & Thomas Hobbs
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe conducts his Collegium Vocale Gent in this chamber music program dedicated to the music of J. S. Bach. On the program are Bach's Orchestral Suite No. 4 in D major, BWV 1069 Gott der Herr ist Sonn und Schild, BWV 79 and Missa brevis in G major, BWV 236. The soloists are soprano Dorothee Mields, tenor Thomas Hobbs, countertenor Alex Potter, and bass Peter Kooij. The program continues with a fine selection of Bach's works performed by French lutenist Thomas Dunford. On the program are Suite for lute in G minor, BWV 995 Suite for solo cello in G major (arr. for lute), BWV 1007 and Chaconne from Partita for solo violin in D minor (arr. lute), BWV 1004. This concert was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, in 2017.

programme.title: Raphael Pichon, Ensemble Pygmalion, Sabine Devieilhe & Arnaud de Pasquale
programme.sub-title: Mozart - A Gala for the Weber Sisters
programme.desc: On March 23, 1783, Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart gave a successful concert at Vienna's Burgtheater that he dedicated to two sopranos: Aloysia and Josepha Weber, the sisters of his wife Constanze. The concert's program would be considered odd by today's standards. The composer's Symphony No. 35 was broken up and interspersed with other compositions, such as concertos, arias, and works for solo piano. Nearly two and a half centuries later, French soprano Sabine Devieilhe, conductor Raphaël Pichon and his Ensemble Pygmalion bring a wonderful concert inspired by that remarkable event. The program includes: ‘Allegro con spirito' of Symphony No. 35, also known as the Haffner Symphony ‘Vorrei spiegarvi, oh Dio', KV 418 ‘Schon lacht der holde Frühling', KV 580 Trio of ‘Die Schlittenfahrt' No. 3, KV 605 Deutscher Tanz No. 6, KV 571 ‘Der Hölle Rache kocht in meinem Herzen' from Mozart's opera Die Zauberflöte ‘Finale: Presto' of Symphony No. 35 ‘Nehmt meinen Dank', KV 383 and ‘Dans un bois solitaire et sombre', KV 308. This performance was recorded at Théâtre Impérial de Compiègne, in Compiègne, France.

programme.title: Jodie Devos, Anaik Morel & David Violi
programme.sub-title: Tribute to French Romanticism at Venice
programme.desc: Salon Romantique à Venise salutes the work of the Palazzetto Bru Zane foundation which aims to contribute to the rediscovery of a neglected part of the French musical heritage running from Louis XVi to WW I. This concert offers a journey into the French romantic repertoire performed by pianist David Violi (piano), Jodie Devos (soprano) and Anaik Morel (mezzo-soprano). The program contains some of the most beloved French arias, such as 'Seguedille' from Bizet's Carmen by Bizet, the Flower Duet from Delibes' Lakmé and 'Mon cœur s'ouvre à ta voix' from Saint-Saëns Samson et Dalila. Recorded at the Palazzetoo Bru Zane in Venice, Italy in 2016.

programme.title: Rodolfo Mederos, Otros Aires, Teresa Parodi & Café de los Maestros
programme.desc: For the audience in the famous ballroom El Palacio in Buenos Aires, the year 2012 began with tango rhythms and Argentinean folk music. This festive broadcast opens with a tango performance by dance partners Eduardo and Gloria, accompanied by the renowned ensemble Café de los Maestros. Another highlights is a performance by bandoneon player Rodolfo Mederos and his trio. In addition, the concert features a performance by Teresa Parodi, former lead singer of the Astor Piazzolla Band, accompanied by the Fernando Suárez Paz Quintet. Also on the bill is the contemporary electronic tango formation Otros Aires. Founded by Miguel Di Genova in 2003, Otros Aires combines electronic rhythms and traditional tango instruments, such as the bandoneon, piano, and guitar. On the program are compositions by Astor Piazzolla, Pedro Maffia, Pedro Laurenz, Gustavo Mozzi, and many others. Enjoy this concert of music and dance, featuring some of Argentine's tango scene's finest artists!

programme.title: Federico Guglielmo & Roberto Loreggian
programme.sub-title: Works by Matteis, Tartini, Bach & Vivaldi
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Federico Guglielmo (violin) and Roberto Loreggian (harpsichord) present Baroque music. On the program are Nicola Matteis's Passaggio rotto e Andamento veloce per violino solo (from Ayres for the Violini), Giuseppe Tartini's Sonata in G minor Op. 1 No. 10 (B.g10) “Didone abbandonata”, J. S. Bach's Concerto in F major for solo harpsichord, BWV 978 (a transcription of Antonio Vivaldi's Violin Concerto in G major, Op. 3 No. 3, RV 310), and Vivaldi's Sonata IV in D major, RV 755.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - String Quartet No. 7 & 13, and Op. 133
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 7 in F major, Op. 59, No. 1, known as “Razumovsky” String Quartet No. 13 in B-flat major, Op. 130 and the monumental Great Fugue, Op. 133. This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 12, 2020.

Arriving just at dawn, you'll enjoy a stunning golden sunrise and rainbow, followed by a couple hours of beautiful beach scenes as you explore the beautiful resort surroundings. Abundant, vibrant vistas will instantly transform your screen into a window to the glorious Caribbean - with nothing but the pure sounds of nature to accompany it. (Music version coming soon though)

programme.title: Dolphin Voyage Relaxation
programme.desc: Replace your worries with wonder as you journey into the deep blue calming ocean with a pod of friendly dolphins in this new 1-hour long film. "Dolphin Voyage Relaxation" is 1-hour long and features some spectacular underwater cinematography by Peter Schneider and a synergistic blend of audio including underwater nature sounds, calming ambient music by The Cynic Project, and a subtle background layer of harmonically tuned binaural relaxation sounds by Schmidt. The result is an immersive, awe-inspiring adventure with gracefully transitions, leaving the viewer with a powerful dose of calm and healing energy direct from Nature.

programme.title: A Day in Santorini
programme.desc: Turn any screen into a window the the Greek Islands with this immensely relaxing HD visual journey through the unique and beautiful coastal village of Oia, found on the far tip of Santorini Island. Slowly awaken your senses as the morning sun rises over the sea, and watch as day slowly passes into dusk. Distant waves break and birds chirp adding an a nice ambient music that combines to create a video that's so relaxing it's almost trance-inducing.
